    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="window-grid">
        <div class="window-body reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">The window</p>
          <h2>Why the first<br />30 days change<br />everything.</h2>
          <p>
            Your body just went through one of the most physically demanding
            events of your life. Childbirth involves profound blood loss and a
            massive expenditure of vital energy. Traditional Chinese medicine
            describes the postpartum body as in a state of deficiency, stasis,
            and cold — more open and more vulnerable than it has ever been.
          </p>
          <p>
            But vulnerability is also opportunity. That same openness makes this
            window uniquely powerful for healing. With the right nourishment and
            the right sequence, a woman can not only recover fully — she can
            emerge with a stronger constitution than she had before pregnancy.
          </p>
          <p class="window-quote">
            “In Chinese tradition, the first month after birth is not a burden
            to endure — it is the most important gift a woman can give herself.”
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
